My molar...

808
00:54:11,391 --> 00:54:13,016
I think I've cracked my jaw!

809
00:54:13,475 --> 00:54:15,266
Stop playing around!

810
00:54:17,725 --> 00:54:19,516
This is so good. Try some.

811
00:54:21,350 --> 00:54:22,308
Try it.

812
00:54:22,891 --> 00:54:23,891
How is it?

813
00:54:24,433 --> 00:54:25,475
It's good.

814
00:54:25,974 --> 00:54:27,683
-Is it good?
-It's good!

815
00:54:30,849 --> 00:54:33,266
If we don't turn off our own spotlights,

816
00:54:34,141 --> 00:54:36,558
if we never give up on our dreams,

817
00:54:36,808 --> 00:54:43,058
we may be able to create
our very own fairy tales.

818
00:54:45,141 --> 00:54:46,600
For example...

819
00:54:47,141 --> 00:54:52,475
"Doldol was happy to
find himself back with his family."

820
00:54:55,808 --> 00:54:59,516
"There was a bright red mailbox
in front of Sookhui's house."

821
00:55:00,641 --> 00:55:04,516
"And at a very young age, Sookhui..."

822
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:05,725
Hey!

823
00:55:17,350 --> 00:55:19,516
They say that first-loves
are impossible in real life,

824
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:21,308
but when they happen,

825
00:55:22,350 --> 00:55:25,767
and when you recover dreams
from when you were a child,

826
00:55:26,391 --> 00:55:30,516
you never know when miracles
will come and find you.

827
00:55:54,183 --> 00:55:55,308
Give me your hand.

828
00:55:59,932 --> 00:56:01,725
It's go time!

829
00:56:06,725 --> 00:56:07,808
Let's go.

830
00:56:14,891 --> 00:56:16,141
Yeonwoo!

831
00:56:16,808 --> 00:56:19,058
Let's hurry up. Your mom's waiting.

832
00:56:30,613 --> 00:56:35,013
"Thank you for watching 'She Was Pretty'"

833
00:56:47,214 --> 00:56:48,614
"She Was Pretty"
